What you’re seeing isn’t random—your modal is jumping to the top because your error-handling + scroll logic is firing on every state change, not just when a real “new error” appears.

Right now, clicking a radio button updates formData → triggers re-render → your useEffect runs → it thinks there’s a “new error state” → calls focusFirstError() → scrolls to top.

